metadata.name: üï∏(üåå,üß†) [neu(t)rons spacetime fabric] #16
metadata.description:
A set of 2 359 296 particles follow the ebbs and flows of a digital spacetime field. 

Ruled by simple particle physics algorithms, this simulation allows to contemplate the similarities between stellar and neural dynamics, galactic and brain matters.

Each one of the 60 frames per second is a unique generative composition.

(Click ‚Äòopen‚Äô to see fullscreen, use wheel/pinch to zoom micro/macro )

-----
Technics

This experience is designed to be executed on a recent GPU (>2016) and displayed on 16/9 screens from FHD to 8K+ (1920x1080 ‚Üí 7680x4320) at 60FPS.

- JavaScript / ThreeJS / WebGL
- Unique generative animation
- Unlimited duration (no loop)
- 1 second to 3 minutes internal algorithm variations
- 5 equiprobable color palettes¬†: white, blue, light blue, green, gold

-----
Controls
Wheel/pinch¬†: zoom in/out to observe the phenomenon on different scales
Right click + drag¬†: move the observation area

metadata.name: Tessera #83
metadata.description:
Tessera is a project inspired by historical Mosaics. A tessera (Latin) is a small individual tile, usually formed in the shape of a square, used for making a mosaic. As the world's first "pixel art", Tessera is a tribute to this craft. This collection is made solely of rectangles on a two-dimensional canvas into an abstract mosaic flow with a three-dimensional effect.

Press s in live mode to download.

Download a higher resolution by adding to the URL:
&density=2 / &density=3 / &density=4

Lammetje Oktober 2022

metadata.name: tratti #180
metadata.description:
"tratti" is an Italian word that has many different meanings. When we started working on this piece, we wanted to create something that combines our traits ("tratti" in Italian).
We had this urge to channel the turbulent times we're living in now into this artwork using just lines ("tratti" in Italian).

We don't know what to do now, we're here, and that's all that matters. We're here for our families, our friends, and our community. Like everything in life, there are joyful times and challenging times. We must accept happiness as something that is not constant but that we feel at times (a "tratti" in Italian).

With "tratti", we want to send a message to every disheartened human being: "Stay strong and never let anyone or anything crush the hope in you. Joyful times are around the corner".

----

metadata.name: Sparsely Populated Grid #155
metadata.description:
‚ÄúSparsely Populated Grid‚Äù is the result of an architect‚Äôs fascination with Cartographies and a crypto-enthusiast love for Neo Punk aesthetics. The first sketch, drawn by hand with Procreate, was made in October 2021.

This is an exploration on the field of Generative Cartographies, an abstract diagrammatic representation of a randomly generated area within the virtual IPFS world. Everything starts with an GRID of varying sizes and angles, subsequently POPULATED by a random number of forms. But, how to populate the grid? SPARSELY, of course, with just the right amount of superpositions.

The algorithm produces varying compositions of fourteen different forms, with seven possible mixes and ten colour palettes. Movement, made possible by its generative digital nature, follows sinusoidal patterns, as if the forms breathed and danced to an unheard music.

Besides, they never forget to celebrate birthdays.


// INTERACTIVITY

- CLICK or SPACEBAR to stop movement.
- UP and DOWN ARROWS to Disable/Enable graphic elements such as texts (wink).
- LEFT and RIGHT ARROWS (when stopped) to Move frames back and forth.
- Press 1 for a low-res PNG.
- Press 2 for a medium-res PNG (3x).
- Press 3 for a hi-res PNG (6x).
- Press G for Glitch (low-res).
- Press P for PixelArt (low-res).

If you want a different resolution, you can also add ?&res=xxx to the url to get your desired output. Then simply Right-Click SAVE the canvas -- experimental

metadata.name: Fractured Cells #92
metadata.description:
Poisson disc sampling of a noise field masked to a shape, and then Voronoi tessellation. Rendered in hand-drawn lines.

Press 's' to take a screenshot. The image size is 1000x1000. 

Features
- 48 curated possible palettes
- 4 possible color distribution methods
- 3 possible shapes: one circle, random circles, circles distributed based on a quadtree 
- 1 to 3 levels of polygon smoothing
- polygon outlines
- polygon fill density and direction
- hand-drawn line roughness

Rare features
- 1 circle
- no polygon smoothing
- background polygons offset from foreground
- color distribution to have a "striped" appearance

metadata.name: CENTURY-XXX-METAFRANKE #481
metadata.description:
1 of 5 in CENTURY-XXX, Series 2
Edition of 1000

Tribute to Herbert W. Franke
‚ÄúIn Honor of the Dinosaur of Computer Art‚Äù 

Herbert W. Franke, a pioneer of computer art, passed away on July 16, 2022 at the age of 95. CENTURY-XXX-METAFRANKE is an homage to Franke‚Äôs MONDRIAN software developed for the Texas Instruments TI 99/4 home computer in 1979, and it‚Äôs a fundraiser to digitize his archive:

‚ÄúOur goal is to raise 20,000 Euro so that ZKM Karlsruhe can digitize Herbert W. Franke‚Äôs 1,800 manuscripts and make them publicly available. If we raise more money, it will be donated to the R√ºtgers Foundation which supports children and young adults in Africa so that they can get access to and work with technology.‚Äù 

Each frame, a single ‚Äúpixel‚Äù is added to the CENTURY-XXX-METAFRANKE image. When the software first loads, 100,000 frames are run in the background to start things off. Keep it running for hours or days to see it transform entirely ‚Äî it‚Äôs an ‚Äúinfinite animation.‚Äù

metadata.name: Holons #100
metadata.description:
Everything is divisible. Larger organisms are made up of smaller ones, entire galaxies are comprised of stars, planets, people, dust, and one effect here and now ripples into eternity. Nothing exists without the elemental components that have evolved to make them possible ‚Äî and nothing on the plane of existence arrives in isolation from something greater. This enmeshed reality is the concept of a Holon: a whole that is simultaneously part of another whole. 

As cells, energies, beings, and ideas grow in complexity, each new advancement includes and transcends their holons, the very catalysts of evolution. What does this essential process look like on its own when scale, context, and definition are removed? The senses are forced to purely observe the present interactions and reactions that occur between all parts. This is what Holons attempts to portray ‚Äî the witnessing of birth, formation, and crystallization simultaneously. 

Upon viewing each piece and inspecting its detail with curiosity ‚Äî we can observe living reality that has been temporarily suspended from motion and artificially stopped for us to witness. Can we see what is a part, and what is a whole? Can we define what these holons are? 

Let each Holons remind us that the impossible can always be made; let each one be nothing and everything ‚Äî organisms, cosmos, energy itself ‚Äî all at once, for it‚Äôs the creation of something entirely new that best reminds us that everything is actually made of the parts already here. So, remember to create without barriers or limitations because reality itself is made of that which lives now only in imagination.


--------

TENDER x flight404
October 2022

Press ‚Äòh‚Äô in live view to render a high resolution version of any token.
Press ‚Äòs‚Äô in live view to save a .png of the current view of any token.

Holons was created in vanilla Javascript and WebGL, but the majority of the work was done in GLSL shaders. This setup was substantially assisted by fx(hash) community leader and artist Liam Egan who provided technical assistance and emotional support during the project's lifespan. For this reason, we have included him in the split of proceeds.

metadata.name: Cloverfield #36
metadata.description:
"Nature is the source of all true knowledge".

Have you ever taken the time to look, deeply look, at all the details in a humble patch of grass ?

In this tiny microcosm, a constant, fierce battle is going on, day after day, plants reaching out for sun, down for access to soil, fighting for survival. Smaller grasses form groups, alliances making it harder for taller ones to take over. Dead leaves remind us that some of them lost the fight, fallen warriors who, soon enough, will be forgotten too. Growth, decay, life, death, the endless cycle, right in front of our eyes.

It is fascinating, and, for me at least, an endless source of inspiration.

It is my hope that, through this project, you will take the time to take a closer look at nature, and that, as the pale blue dot we call home keeps getting drier and drier, remember that even humble patches of grass should not be taken for granted.


Key commands:
's' - save as png
'b' - make the background transparent (for printing)
'1', '2, '4' - set the pixel density, for resolutions up to 8000x8000

This updated version of the project should render on mobile devices, albeit with slightly reduced quality. 
If you want to save the image for printing, I recommend you do so on desktop.

metadata.name: Ethereal Microcosm #2
metadata.description:
An exploration of algorithmic organisms in a contained environment.

This piece is about the simulation of microscopic patterns using a high number of even tinier agents all following the same rules. Different species evolve and interact together, resulting in stabilizing patterns out of their parametric configurations. A form of artificial life.

This work is based on the paper "Characteristics of pattern formation and evolution in approximations of physarum transport networks", written by Jeff Jones and popularized in the artistic field by Sage Jenson. Some features were added to increase the visual and behavioral complexity of the system. Agents are divided into different species, with their own set of rules and interacting with their own substrate. Substrates also interact with each other and agents will mutate in contact of some of them.
